      <hedline>
        <hl1>Debating Global Warming</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robynne Curlee letter on December 3 article on global warming questions why Pres George Bush is avoiding action</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Scientists are at a virtual consensus that climate change does exist, it is a threat to humans, and the time to act is now (''Global Warming''). Yet the president continues to avoid action.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Scientists are at a virtual consensus that climate change does exist, it is a threat to humans, and the time to act is now (''Global Warming''). Yet the president continues to avoid action.</p>
        <p>Corporations contribute millions and are rewarded with initiatives that delay action on climate change and increase dependence on fossil fuels. Ordinary citizens may not have millions of dollars for buying policy, but we do have a vested interest. We want to ensure a safe environment for future generations. Clearly President Bush does not share this concern.</p>
        <p>ROBYNNE CURLEE  St. Paul</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
